Package: mlr3autoiml
Type: Package
Title: Automated Gate-Based Auditing for Interpretable Machine Learning in 'mlr3'
Version: 0.0.6
Authors@R: c(
    person("Stefan", "Coors", email = "mail@stefancoors.de", role = c("aut","cre")),
    person("Clara", "Vetter", role = "aut"),
    person("Jonas", "Hauck", role = "aut"),
    person("Bernd", "Bischl", role = "aut"),
    person("Sven", "Hilbert", role = "aut")
  )
Description: Implements a gate-based AutoIML workflow (G0A/G0B, G1-G6, G7A/G7B) for mlr3 Tasks and Learners.
    Produces task- and data-dependent interpretability artifacts (ALE/ICE, interaction screening,
    calibration and decision utility incl. recalibration and OVR multiclass checks, local faithfulness
    stress tests, multiplicity and shift probes, subgroup audits, and audit-ready report cards)
    with minimal dependencies. Version 0.0.6 aligns claim-scoped IEL assignment and audit-bundle
    requirements with the manuscript workflow, including audience-aware Gate 7B triggering and
    applicability-aware evidence checks in the extended report card.
